2) Comparing to a time window â€“ Percentile and Mean/Median difference representations: In order to explicitly include temporal information and reï¬‚ect changes in user activities, we propose to represent data for anomaly detection via a function comparing each data instance ğ‘¥ğ‘¡ with a time window ğ‘¤ leading to ğ‘¡. The procedure is summarized in Algorithm 1.
Each arriving data instance is compared with previous data instances of the same user in the most recent time window ğ‘¤ to create percentile or mean/median difference representation. In this work, we set the window size ğ‘¤ to 7 days, 30 days, or 60 days (IV-A). This setting allows contrasting each day (week) of userâ€™s activity against the same userâ€™s activities in the full week (month) leading to it, where both weekdays and weekends are taken into account to provide sufï¬cient information for comparison.

