Post training, the lossy compression produced by AE essentially captures the lower-dimensionality representation of the majority of training data at the middle hidden layer. Assuming that normal user data constitute the majority of the training data, it is expected that AE shows a higher reconstruction error for anomalies [38], which may represent malicious insider behaviours. Thus, for each data instance ğ‘¥, the AE anomaly

score is deï¬ned as the Euclidean distance between ğ‘¥ and ğ‘Ÿ: âˆšï¸ƒ

